      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="807-ROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">AN EPIGRAM</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-1"> Would you rise in the church, be stupid and dull,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-2"> Be empty of learning, of insolence full:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-3"> Though lewd and immoral, be formal and grave,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-4"> In flattery an artist, in fawning a slave,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-5"> No merit, no science, no virtue is wanting</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-6"> In him, that's accomplished in cringing and canting:</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-7"> Be studious to practise true meanness of spirit;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-8"> For who but Lord Bolton was mitred for merit?</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-9"> Would you wish to be wrapped in a rochet──in short,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-807-ROGP-line-10"> Be as poxed and profane as fanatical Hort.807-ROGP   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
